# v0.5.0 — 2026-06-12 — benoitcayladbx

## Fix: Deleted class attributes reappear in OWL export (issue #50)

**Context**: Reported in
[databrickslabs/ontobricks#50](https://github.com/databrickslabs/ontobricks/issues/50).
When an `owl:DatatypeProperty` (a class attribute) was deleted in the ontology
designer, the deleted property reappeared as a `DatatypeProperty` in every
subsequent OWL/Turtle export.

**Root cause**: Domain-scoped datatype properties are stored in two places once
an OWL file is parsed — `classes[].dataProperties` (the authoritative attribute
list the designer mutates) and a shadow entry in the top-level `properties[]`
list (`OntologyParser.get_properties()` legitimately returns every property,
including datatype ones, and `apply_parsed_owl_to_domain` persists both). When
an attribute is deleted in the designer only `classes[].dataProperties` is
updated; the shadow in `properties[]` survives. `OntologyGenerator.generate()`
emits class attributes from *both* paths — `_add_class()` →
`_add_data_property_for_class()` *and* `_add_property()` for the `properties[]`
list — so `_add_property()` re-emitted the stale shadow and the deleted
attribute came back on export.

Changing `get_properties()` to drop datatype properties was rejected: its
contract (and downstream consumers / tests) rely on it returning all
properties. The fix is therefore applied at the single export choke point, the
generator, which treats `classes[].dataProperties` as the source of truth for
class attributes.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyGenerator.py` — added `_local_name()`,
   `_build_class_attr_index()` (built once in `__init__`, maps each class — by
   name and by URI local name — to the set of attribute local names it
   declares) and `_is_stale_datatype_shadow()`. In `_add_property()`, a
   `DatatypeProperty` whose domain class is known but no longer declares that
   attribute is now skipped (logged at debug). The check is conservative: an
   empty domain or an unknown domain class is never dropped, so object
   properties, domain-less datatype properties and surviving attributes
   (including their declared range, e.g. `xsd:integer`) are unaffected.
2. `tests/units/ontology/test_owl_generator.py` — added
   `TestDeletedAttributeNotReexported` with four regression tests: stale shadow
   skipped, surviving shadow (and its range) kept, unknown-domain datatype
   property kept, and a full parse → delete-attribute → regenerate round-trip.

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyGenerator.py`
- `tests/units/ontology/test_owl_generator.py`

**Test result**: `python -m pytest tests/units --ignore=tests/property` →
**2277 passed, 15 skipped**. The two new reproduction tests fail before the fix
and pass after it; the two conservative-behaviour tests pass throughout.
(`tests/property/test_owl_roundtrip.py` is skipped — the `hypothesis` package is
not installed in this environment, unrelated to this change.)
